assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Itochu Enex Co.,Ltd. engages in the sale of petroleum products and liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) in Japan and internationally. It operates through four divisions: Home-Life, Car-Life, Industrial Business, and Power & Utility. The Home-Life division is involved in the sale of LPG, town gas, industrial gas, specialty gas, electricity, and kerosene; gas for medical and automotive usage; household and smart energy equipment; solar power systems; ENEFARM residential fuel cells; ENE-POWABOL residential lithium-ion electricity storage systems; and welding materials, as well as supply of LPG and city gas to 1.5 million households. This division also engages in the remodeling and gas container pressure resistance inspection businesses. The Car-Life division sells gasoline, kerosene, diesel oil, electricity, automobiles, and lifestyle and automotive products; offers credit card services and IT support services; and rents cars. This division also operates approximately 1,636 car-life gas stations and 452 rent-a-car service stores. The Industrial Business division sells gasoline, kerosene, diesel and fuel oil, gas to liquids fuel, marine fuel, LPG, corporate fleet refueling card, and asphalt, as well as high-grade urea solution; and engages in the recycling of fly ash, recovery and recycling of slop, import/export and trading of petroleum products, and rental of terminal tanks. The Power & Utility division engages in the sale of electricity from coal-fired, natural gas-fired, wind, hydro, and photovoltaic power; and sells steam. This division also offers district heating, energy, electricity/heat supply, and electricity power supply/demand management, as well as asset management services. The company was formerly known as Itochu Fuel Corporation and changed its name to Itochu Enex Co.,Ltd. in July 2001. The company was founded in 1961 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan. Itochu Enex Co.,Ltd. is a subsidiary of ITOCHU Corporation.
